reviewText: Awesome stuff great anime and manga!
One Piece is by far my favorite anime of all time. I preordered this and got it the same day in the mail.
The best voyage there is going to be released watched it all in Japanese and this next voyage will blow your mind no spoilers but somebody is going to die in this one!!!!¡!¡!!!¡!!
This series could go on and on, and I would keep watching.
What else can I say? If you love One Piece then you want this.
DAMN IT... it getting there... loving tha dub!

My typical conflicted One Piece anime review: on the one hand, it follows the well written plot of the utterly fantastic manga quite well. On the other hand, the animation is shit and each episode contains about 15 minutes of meaningless stock footage because Toei is the cheapest anime studio in the industry. The dub is okay. It's not FUNimation's best, but not their worst. The biggest issue seems to be that there are simply too many characters for FUNi to be able to cast every character as well as they could be. Overall, if you have made it this far in the series, do you really need a recommendation? Either you like One Piece or don't at this point. If you do, you can tolerate the extremely low quality animation in order to get to the story that you know and love. Recommended to fans of the series, but not really anyone else.
Love One Piece! Can't wait for more!

I love the show, Keep bringing them out Funimation!

And to everyone out there asking if you should buy them, please do. Support One Piece in english and they will keep releasing more. I simply love it.
